race.comment: GIDEON'S RIOT (1) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 17.40 when a 4.5 lengths winner over 300m at this track last time. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. One of the key runners again. BIG COOL KAOS (5) is looking to continue his winning ways off a blistering 17.36 success at this track. Smart winner latest and looks a key chance on that form. CROSSED TOES (2) is a safe beginner. Latest effort finished 4th in a Grade 5 on October 17 over 400m at The Gardens behind Zipping Bubbles beaten 9 lengths (23.66). Looks suited here and can measure up. RETURN AN EARN (7) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to turn the form around.
